Happy NYE! Wow, the posts about RESOLUTIONS are filling up my IG scrolling this morning. And it definitely can feel overwhelming.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So I have a question for you: What if your only resolution was to LIVE MORE JOYFULLY?

JOY IS A NUTRIENT which means joy is something that’s NECESSARY for overall well-being and health. JOY can boost immunity, keep the stress hormone cortisol in check, and keep motivation to eat right and exercise strong. 

The secret to boosting joy is cultivating: 1) more gratitude AND 2) more play in your life. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here are 6 ideas of ways to live more joyfully in 2023: 

1. Gratitude shower. Use your time in the shower to thank each body part for all it does for you. 

2. Real-time gratitude. Notice super small things all through the day that you are grateful for like the perfect temperature coffee, having your car get you safely to work, or being able to pick up heavy groceries. Having a typical gratitude journal is fine, but when you start noticing the REALLY SMALL STUFF IN REAL-TIME, that’s what really helps amplify daily joy.

3. Playful physical activities. Do active stuff you liked as a kid such as jump rope (you know I love this!), hoola hoop, hopscotch, and dancing.

4. Playful creative activities. Do stimulating stuff you liked as a kid such as crafts, draw, color, and puzzles.

5. Try something new. New things spark fun and play such as try a new fitness class, new hobby, new restaurant, or new food or recipe.

6. Random acts of kindness. Doing good for others in even small ways spikes your own joy, so it’s a win-win. Hold the door for someone, compliment someone, or send an email of appreciate to a friend or co-worker.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you're finding resolution talk overwhelming, consider a shift to prioritizing JOY! Enjoy the last day of 2022 and see you next year. ❌⭕️❌⭕️

#ad In celebration of February being HEART ❤️ HEALTH MONTH, I have a new oatmeal recipe for you: Protein Latte Overnight Oats. This recipe has all of the goodness of oats, and it tastes like a latte!☕️ And since I often eat this after workouts, I like the added scoop of protein.💪

Oats are highly versatile, offering countless possibilities to add more taste and nutrition into what we eat each day. @quaker Oats are a convenient source of fiber, and provide the soluble fiber “beta-glucan,” which may help to lower cholesterol levels and reduce the risk for heart disease. 3g of soluble fiber from oats as part of a diet low in saturated fat and cholesterol may help reduce the risk of heart disease. A serving of Old Fashioned oats provides 2 grams.

👉PROTEIN LATTE OVERNIGHT OATS (makes 1 serving)

1/2 cup Quaker Old Fashioned Oats
1 scoop vanilla plant protein powder (~15-20 grams protein)
1/2 cup unsweetened plant milk
1/4 cup strong brewed coffee (can be hot or cold; or ~1/2 teaspoon instant coffee)
1/2 tablespoon ground flaxseed 
1/4 cup blueberries or raspberries

1. In a jar, whisk (or shake) together protein powder, milk, and coffee until smooth.
2. Stir in Quaker Old Fashioned Oats and flaxseed and cover.
3. Let sit in fridge overnight. 
4. When you’re ready to eat, stir, top with berries, and enjoy. Or if you prefer warm oats, heat in the microwave for 30 seconds before putting on the berries.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
NOTES: 
- This is a great way to use leftover coffee.
- Make multiple jars to have in the fridge for the week.

#quaker #oats #wholegrain #fiber #hearthealth #coffee #latte #protein #overnightoats #ONO

Shift your EATING ATTITUDE before meals & snacks.
The intention/energy you bring to eating is powerful. It can make your meals & snacks less nutritious and emotionally toxic OR... deeply nourishing and enjoyable.
Do a 4-point check before eating to shift your vibe:
1. Calm (not stressed)
2. Mindful (not distracted)
3. Ownership (not shame)

2 tablespoons maple syrup

1/2 teaspoon cumin

⚡️LOADED HUMMUS & GRILLED CHICKEN SKEWERS⚡️
INGREDIENTS
2 containers hummus (your favorite flavor)
1 cup chopped cucumber
1 cup chopped tomatoes
1/4 cup pitted/chopped kalamata olives
1/4 cup finely chopped red onion
1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese
2 tablespoons chopped fresh dill
2 pounds skinless chicken breast
2 tablespoons olive oil
1/2 teaspoon each: paprika, sea salt, black pepper
1 bag lentil chips

DIRECTIONS
Spread the hummus on a platter/serving dish.
Top with cucumber, tomatoes, olives, onion, feta, dill, and set aside.
Cut chicken into 1” pieces, toss with oil, paprika, salt, and pepper, and thread on skewers.
Grill chicken skewers for about 12-15 minutes, flipping as they cook, until the chicken is an internal temperature of 165° F.
Note: If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for 30 minutes before adding on the chicken.
Serve the skewers next to or right on top of the loaded hummus.
Enjoy the loaded hummus with lentil chips.

Croutons, but better! #ad SWEETPOTATO CROUTONS are one of my favorite tricks to making a salad naturally more satisfying & nutritious.🍠

These croutons are ready in just 15 minutes, with the help of your air-fryer. (No air-fryer, no problem! You can also make these in the oven.)

And the best part is SWEETPOTATOES are an ORANGE SUPERFOOD full of important nutrients.
Each medium SWEETPOTATO has:
🧡 only about 100 CALORIES
🧡 QUALITY CARBS (for steady energy)
🧡 FIBER (4 grams which is more than in a packet of oatmeal!)
🧡 VITAMIN A (over 100% of your daily needs)
🧡 VITAMIN C (immune boosting antioxidant)
🧡 ELECTROLYTES like 440mg potassium, 70mg sodium, and 32mg magnesium

🍠SWEETPOTATO CROUTONS🍠
1 large sweetpotato (or 2 medium sweetpotatoes)
1 tablespoon olive oil
1/2 teaspoon each: black pepper, garlic powder, onion powder
1/4 teaspoon sea salt
Pre-heat air-fryer to 400 degrees F.
Wash the sweetpotato and cut into 1/2 “ cubes (leaving the peel on).
Toss with olive oil, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt.
Cook sweetpotato cubes in the air-fryer for 12-15 minutes, shaking once midway, until the cubes are golden and crisp.

Pro-Tips: 
- Don’t overcrowd the air-fryer, cook in two batches if necessary.
- Eat them right away or refrigerate for up to 4 days. If you want them hot & crispy from the fridge, reheat them in a 400 degree F air-fryer for 3-4 minutes.
-  If using an oven, cook the sweetpotato cubes at 425 degrees F for 25-30 minutes, flipping midway.

🏈GIANT SHEET PAN QUESADILLA🏈
INGREDIENTS
1 tablespoon olive oil, and extra for brushing
2 bell peppers, any color, chopped
1 onion, chopped
2 tablespoons taco seasoning
2 cups shredded rotisserie chicken
1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro
1 jalapeño, finely diced
8 whole grain 10” tortillas
2 cans (16 oz each) vegetarian refried beans
2 cups shredded cheddar cheese
Toppers: lime slices, mashed avocado, salsa, sour cream

DIRECTIONS
- Heat oven to 425 degrees F.
- In a skillet over medium heat, add olive oil, bell peppers, onion, and taco seasoning and cook for about 5 mins, until tender.
- Remove skillet from heat. In the skillet, stir together the cooked veggies, shredded chicken, jalapeño, and cilantro. Set aside.
- Brush oil on a 13x18 sheet pan and lay 4 tortillas around the edge of the sheet pan, with half of each tortilla hanging over the rim. Add 2 more tortillas in the center so the entire sheet pan is covered.
- Spread on refried beans (warm them if they are too hard to spread), top with veggie & chicken filling, and sprinkle on cheese. 
- Top with 2 tortillas in the center, and fold over each of the tortillas so all of the filling is covered.
- Brush tortillas with oil, place another baking sheet on top to hold down the quesadilla, and bake for 20 mins. 
- Remove the top baking sheet and bake an extra 8 mins, until golden.
- Let cool for about 5 mins, and then with a pizza cutter, cut 8 large pieces and serve with lime slices, mashed avocado, salsa, and sour cream.

🎃PUMKIN FRENCH TOAST MUFFINS🎃
INGREDIENTS
12 pieces sprouted whole grain bread
6 eggs
1 cup plain 2% Greek yogurt
3/4 cup canned pumpkin
6 tablespoons maple syrup
1 heaping tablespoon pumpkin pie spice

DIRECTIONS
- Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees F.
- Cut bread into 1” cubes, set aside. 
- In a large bowl, whisk eggs and then mix in yogurt, pumpkin, maple syrup, and pumpkin pie spice.
- Lightly stir/fold bread and evenly spoon mixture into 12 muffin tins.
- Bake 30 minutes, until golden. Let cool for 15 minutes & enjoy!
- Store leftovers in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 3 days, in the fridge up to 7 days, or freeze for up to 3 months.
- PS: I think they are best eaten a little warm from the oven or microwave.

KALE & CHEDDAR EGG BITES.🍃🧀🍳These Egg Bites are great to make on the weekend so you can enjoy them for quick breakfasts or snacks throughout the week. They also make great party appetizers.

Store them covered in the fridge for up to 4 days or freeze them for up to 2 months. Each bite has 8g of protein!

Ingredients
2 cups chopped kale 1/2 tablespoon olive oil (+ a little extra for brushing) 12 eggs 1/2 teaspoon each sea salt & pepper 3/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese

Directions
1. Cook kale in 1/2 tablespoon olive oil. 2. Brush a little olive oil into a 12-cup muffin pan and add about 2 tablespoons of sauteed kale into each cup. 3. Whisk eggs with salt & pepper and pour evenly into the muffin pan. 4. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese on each. 5. Bake 350 degrees F for about 18-20 minutes, until eggs are set.

Pro-Tips: – I use a silicone muffin pan & the egg bites come out of it perfectly! – I love the combo of kale & cheddar, but you can use other sauteed veggies or cheese like mushrooms & swiss or spinach & parmesan. – Reheat in the microwave for ~30 seconds from the fridge or ~60+ seconds from the freezer. Or reheat in a toaster oven or under the broiler.

SWEETPOTATOES are an ORANGE SUPERFOOD full of important nutrients. 
Each medium SWEETPOTATO has:
🧡 only about 100 CALORIES
🧡 QUALITY CARBS (for steady energy)
🧡 FIBER (4 grams which is more than in a packet of oatmeal!)
🧡 VITAMIN A (over 100% of your daily needs)
🧡 VITAMIN C (immune boosting antioxidant)
🧡 ELECTROLYTES like 440mg potassium, 70mg sodium, and 32mg magnesium

🍠SWEETPOTATO HASHBROWN WAFFLES (aka “SWAFFLES”)🍠
Makes 4 swaffles

2 medium sweetpotatoes
2 eggs, whisked
1/2 teaspoon sea salt
Olive oil, for brushing

- Pre-heat a waffle maker and wash/dry sweetpotatoes.
- Shred sweetpotatoes using a box grater (it should be ~4 cups).
- Mix eggs and salt into the grated sweetpotatoes.
- Brush waffle maker with olive oil, add 1/4 of the sweetpotato mixture, and spread it out evenly. 
- Close the waffle maker and cook for about 6 minutes, or longer if you’d like them more crisp.

PS: SWAFFLES keep in fridge for up to 4 days and freezer up to 3 months. They are great reheated in an air-fryer or toaster.

STOP CALLING CERTAIN FOODS “FUN FOODS.”

I just saw a nutrition program created by a doctor that says it allows 5% “fun foods” like cookies, candy, ice cream, chips, etc. UGH! NOOO!!!!!!

🚩RED FLAG. 

Dude, that’s like saying 95% of your food needs to be UNFUN! And that’s literally the OPPOSITE of what works if you want a lifelong optimal health. You need to have FUN & enjoy your food, whatever you are choosing to eat.

Broccoli can be FUN! Apples can be FUN! Cookies can be FUN! Certain foods aren’t fun or unfun. It’s the VIBE YOU PUT INTO your meals/snacks that determines their FUN FACTOR.

Are some foods healthier than others, heck yes! 
But we don’t need to label foods as “good or bad,” because it implies moral judgement.
And we don’t need to label certain foods as fun, because it implies others aren’t. 

Mic🎤 drop.

Sometimes basic chicken, broccoli, and brown rice hits the spot! Meals should be enjoyable & craveable, but that doesn’t mean they have to be a creative masterpiece every night!

SIMPLE can be craveable!

I have personally created thousands of recipes. And I doomscroll IG daily and am bombarded with thousands of creative recipe ideas.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And all of that can lead to the BIG ISSUE of “DECISION FATIGUE.” Having so many choices, you can’t make a choice!🤯

So if you are ever feeling overwhelmed with food decisions, the answer is… SIMPLIFY! Put in a little love & effort to make yourself a basic meal, and it is surprising how fun & delish it can be!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Even simple meals can easily be changed up with a new veggie, side, sauce, etc. You don’t have to be an elaborate chef to feed yourself well!

Years ago I set-up a text reminder that pops-up on my phone throughout the day that says: "Are you having fun?🎉" It's been a game-changer for me...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It's so easy to get caught up in the low vibes of competition, comparison, deadline stress, perfectionism, unworthiness.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Exercise, making meals, drinking water, working on an important science-y webinar, being on an intimidating business call, getting dressed, etc.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
